      • applySubstitution

        public Literal applySubstitution(Substitution tau,
                        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Variable> vars,
                        long time)
        Constructs a new literal from the application of the given substitution to this literal. (Note: apply ' to distinguish variables with equals name (and different index) example: in case of x_3 and x_4 --> x_newIndex and x'_newIndex
        Parameters:
        tau - substitution
        vars - map of variables and new name given in the results
        time - index of the new clause
        Returns:
        the new literal if the substitution modify the literal this if the substitution has no effects.
